This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald Trump on April 4, 2018, regarding immigration and the need to secure the southern border of the United States. The memorandum highlights the surge of illegal activity, including the flow of drugs and the presence of transnational gangs, which threatens the safety and sovereignty of the country. The President directs the Secretary of Defense to support the Department of Homeland Security in securing the border, including the use of National Guard forces if necessary. The Secretary of Defense is also directed to work with the Secretary of Homeland Security to provide training and instruction to military personnel. Additionally, the Secretaries, in coordination with the Attorney General, are directed to determine other resources and actions necessary to protect the border and submit a report with recommendations within 30 days. The memorandum clarifies that it does not impair existing authorities or create new rights or benefits enforceable against the United States.